# Changelog

All notable changes to aislib are documented in this file.

The format follows [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/).
Version numbers follow [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

---

## [Unreleased]

### Fixed

- `src/messages/msg5.cpp` ‚Äî `kMsg5BitLength` was 424, which is the sum of the
  named content fields only.  ITU-R M.1371-5 Table 47 specifies 426 bits:
  424 content bits plus a 2-bit spare at bits 423‚Äì424.  The constant has been
  corrected to 426.  The `encode()` method now writes the spare as
  `write_uint(0u, 2u)` rather than `write_uint(0u, 1u)`.  426 / 6 = 71 armour
  characters exactly, so the encoded form carries 0 fill bits as documented.

- `include/aislib/messages/msg5.h` ‚Äî the `encode()` Doxygen stated "fill bit
  count will be 2" immediately after stating the payload is 426 bits.  These
  are contradictory: 426 % 6 = 0.  The comment now correctly states that the
  fill bit count is 0, and explains the arithmetic (424 content bits + 2 spare
  bits = 426 = 71 √ó 6).  The file-level comment has been updated to document
  the spare as 2 bits at positions 423‚Äì424.

- `tests/core/test_message.cpp` ‚Äî the `NoDecodersRegisteredInPhase1` test
  asserted that `has_decoder()` returns false for all 27 type IDs.  Because
  `MessageRegistry` is a process-lifetime singleton and GoogleTest does not
  guarantee execution order across translation units, any Phase 2 fixture
  calling `register_all_decoders()` before this test runs would cause it to
  fail.  The test has been converted to a `TEST_F` using a new
  `RegistryIsolation` fixture that calls `clear()` in `SetUp()` and
  `register_all_decoders()` in `TearDown()`, ensuring the singleton is in a
  known state for the duration of each isolation test and restored afterwards.
  `DecodeUnregisteredTypeReturnsUnsupported` has been converted to the same
  fixture for the same reason.  A third `TEST_F` has been added that positively
  verifies the `register_decoder()` / `has_decoder()` round-trip.  Payload
  error tests that fire before dispatch remain plain `TEST()` cases and carry
  no fixture overhead.

- `tests/core/CMakeLists.txt` ‚Äî `pgais_core_tests` now links against
  `pgais_messages` in addition to `pgais_core`.  The `RegistryIsolation`
  fixture calls `register_all_decoders()`, which is defined in
  `src/registry_init.cpp` and compiled into `pgais_messages`.  Without this
  link entry the linker could not resolve the symbol.

- `include/aislib/registry_init.h` ‚Äî the `register_all_decoders()` Doxygen
  previously enumerated the specific type IDs registered in Phase 2.  That
  list becomes stale whenever a new phase merges.  The comment now states the
  invariant ("all message type IDs that have a concrete implementation") and
  directs readers to the CHANGELOG for the current list.

- `tests/messages/test_msg5.cpp` ‚Äî the `build_type5` helper wrote the spare
  field as `write_uint(0u, 1u)` (1 bit), producing a 425-bit buffer.  The
  decoder requires 426 bits, so every test using this helper returned
  `PayloadTooShort` before reading any field.  The spare write has been
  corrected to `write_uint(0u, 2u)` to match the corrected `kMsg5BitLength`.

---

## [0.2.0] ‚Äî 2026-03-11

Implements Phase 2: concrete message decoders for types 1‚Äì5, 11, 18, and 24,
along with the umbrella header and decoder registration infrastructure.

### Added

- `include/aislib/messages/msg1_3.h` / `src/messages/msg1_3.cpp` ‚Äî
  `Msg1_3PositionReportClassA` decodes and encodes ITU-R M.1371-5 message
  types 1 (Scheduled Class A), 2 (Assigned Class A), and 3 (Special Class A).
  All 168-bit fields are covered: MMSI, navigation status, rate of turn,
  speed over ground, position accuracy, longitude, latitude, course over
  ground, true heading, time stamp, and RAIM flag.  Longitude and latitude are
  returned as `std::optional<double>` with automatic sentinel detection
  (`0x6791AC0` and `0x3412140` respectively).  A static `decode(BitReader&)`
  factory and a virtual `encode()` implementation are provided.

- `include/aislib/messages/msg4_11.h` / `src/messages/msg4_11.cpp` ‚Äî
  `Msg4_11BaseStationReport` decodes and encodes message types 4 (Base Station
  Report) and 11 (UTC/Date Response).  The 168-bit payload carries UTC year,
  month, day, hour, minute, second, position accuracy, longitude, latitude,
  EPFD type, and RAIM flag.  Coordinate sentinel detection mirrors the
  Class A decoder.

- `include/aislib/messages/msg5.h` / `src/messages/msg5.cpp` ‚Äî
  `Msg5StaticAndVoyageData` decodes and encodes the two-part 426-bit type 5
  message.  Fields covered: AIS version, IMO number, call sign (7 characters),
  vessel name (20 characters), ship and cargo type, reference point dimensions
  (bow, stern, port, starboard), EPFD type, ETA (month, day, hour, minute),
  draught, destination (20 characters), and DTE flag.  Trailing `@` padding
  and trailing spaces are stripped from all text fields on decode.

- `include/aislib/messages/msg18.h` / `src/messages/msg18.cpp` ‚Äî
  `Msg18ClassBPositionReport` decodes and encodes the 168-bit type 18 message.
  Fields covered: reserved, speed over ground, position accuracy, longitude,
  latitude, course over ground, true heading, time stamp, regional reserved,
  CS flag, display flag, DSC flag, band flag, message 22 flag, assigned flag,
  and RAIM flag.

- `include/aislib/messages/msg24.h` / `src/messages/msg24.cpp` ‚Äî
  `Msg24StaticDataReport` decodes and encodes both parts of the 168-bit type
  24 message.  Part A carries vessel name (20 characters).  Part B carries
  ship type, vendor ID (7 characters), call sign (7 characters), reference
  point dimensions, and EPFD type.  Part A and Part B are independent
  single-part sentences; the decoder branches on the part number field.

- `include/aislib/registry_init.h` / `src/registry_init.cpp` ‚Äî
  `register_all_decoders()` registers decoder functions for all message types
  implemented in Phase 2 (1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 11, 18, 24) with the
  `MessageRegistry` singleton.  Callers must invoke this function once at
  startup before issuing any `MessageRegistry::decode()` calls.

- `include/aislib/aislib.h` ‚Äî umbrella header that includes all Phase 1 and
  Phase 2 public headers in a single include.  Intended for consumers that do
  not need to control include granularity.

- `tests/messages/` ‚Äî 97 unit tests across five files covering all Phase 2
  message types.  Each file provides a `build_*` helper that constructs a
  valid raw bit buffer for the corresponding message, field-level decode tests,
  padding-strip tests, encode/decode round-trip tests, too-short payload error
  tests, wrong-type error tests, and registry dispatch tests.

### Fixed

- `src/core/bitfield.cpp` ‚Äî `BitReader::read_text()` previously delegated
  bounds checking to `check_bounds()`, which enforces a maximum field width of
  64 bits.  A 20-character text field spans 120 bits, causing every multi-char
  text read to return `ErrorCode::BitfieldWidthInvalid`.  The call to
  `check_bounds()` has been replaced with a direct range check
  (`offset + char_count * 6 > bit_length()`), which carries no upper-bound
  restriction.  All existing `ReadText_OutOfRange` tests continue to pass.

---

## [0.1.0] ‚Äî 2026-03-11

Initial release.  Implements the complete Phase 1 core parsing infrastructure.

### Added

- `include/aislib/error.h` ‚Äî `ErrorCode` enum, `Error` class, and `Result<T>`
  discriminated union.  All fallible public APIs return `Result<T>`; no
  exceptions are thrown across library boundaries.

- `include/aislib/bitfield.h` / `src/core/bitfield.cpp` ‚Äî `BitReader` and
  `BitWriter` for packed MSB-first bit-field access over a
  `std::vector<uint8_t>` buffer.  Supports unsigned, signed (two's-complement),
  boolean, 6-bit ASCII text, and raw bit reads and writes.  All operations are
  bounds-checked.

- `include/aislib/payload.h` / `src/core/payload.cpp` ‚Äî NMEA 6-bit ASCII
  armour encode and decode (`decode_payload`, `encode_payload`).  Fill-bit
  handling is explicit in both directions.

- `include/aislib/sentence.h` / `src/core/sentence.cpp` ‚Äî `Sentence::parse()`
  for full NMEA 0183 sentence validation including XOR checksum verification.
  `SentenceAssembler` provides stateful multi-part message reassembly with
  support for concurrent independent sequences keyed by `seq_id`.

- `include/aislib/message.h` / `src/core/message.cpp` ‚Äî `Message` abstract
  base class, `MessageType` enumeration covering all 27 ITU-R M.1371-5 type
  IDs, `message_type_from_id()` helper, and `MessageRegistry` singleton
  providing a decoder dispatch table.  No concrete decoders are registered in
  Phase 1.

- `CMakeLists.txt` ‚Äî C++17 build with strict per-target warning flags and
  `-Werror`.  GoogleTest 1.14.0 fetched via `FetchContent` with warnings
  suppressed during its build and its headers marked `SYSTEM`.  Coverage
  instrumentation available via `-DPGAIS_ENABLE_COVERAGE=ON`.

- `tests/core/` ‚Äî 153 unit tests across six files covering all public APIs,
  all documented error conditions, and encode/decode round-trips.

### Fixed

- `src/core/sentence.cpp` ‚Äî `SentenceAssembler::feed()` now validates that
  every fragment of a multi-part sequence carries the same sentence type
  (VDM or VDO) as the first fragment.  Previously, a sequence opened by a VDM
  sentence could be completed by a VDO sentence, silently producing an
  `AssembledMessage` with an incorrect `is_own_vessel` flag.  The new check
  returns `ErrorCode::MultipartTalkerConflict`.

- `src/core/payload.cpp` ‚Äî replaced a `goto`-based early exit in
  `decode_payload()` with a named static helper `unpack_bits()`.

- `src/core/bitfield.cpp` / `include/aislib/bitfield.h` ‚Äî corrected the
  invalid-input sentinel for `ascii_to_ais6bit()` from 15 to 63, making the
  documented and implemented behaviour consistent.  Value 63 maps back to `'?'`
  via `ais6bit_to_ascii()`, is printable, and is distinct from the padding
  character `'@'` (value 0).